BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:uA--5ZCNPwTlSvxx4A-NC
SUMMARY:IMPROV 100 SATURDAYS- Intro to Improv: Say Yes!\\\, SPRING'26
DTSTAMP:20260306T002950Z
DTSTART:20260321T120000Z
DESCRIPTION:Discover Unexpected Productions’ philosophy of improvisation\\\
	, developed over our 43 years of improvising in Seattle! \\nYou’ll learn h
	ow to actively listen\\\, to use your own life to create collaborative sto
	ries\\\, and you’ll work on the fundamental principles of improvisation: w
	hat it means to say\\\, “Yes\\\, And”\\\, how to tell stories that include
	 everyone in the room\\\, how to stop worrying about failing\\\, and the g
	ames and concepts behind what we do on stages around the world! \\nUnder t
	he guidance of one of our best Seattle improv teachers\\\, you will learn 
	to:· \\n\\nBe a Better Listener\\nConquer Fears\\nSpark Creativity\\nMeet 
	New People & Make New Friends\\nBecome a Better Problem Solver\\nGain Conf
	idence·\\nFail With Grace (and Maybe Even Enjoy It)\\nSay Yes More in Your
	 Life\\nGet Out of Your Comfort Zone\\nBecome a Better Public Speaker\\nDi
	scover More About Yourself\\n…and have a blast doing it!\\n\\nTime and Dat
	es: Saturdays for eight (8) weeks\\\, from March 21 to May 9\\\, 12pm to 2
	:30pm. \\nNOTE: Attendance at the first session of your course is mandator
	y as it sets the agenda for the entire quarter. If you think you will have
	 to miss the first class\\\, please consider registering for the next quar
	ter. \\nNo Prerequisites. All students begin at this level\\\, even those 
	with existing improv experience. It’s a prerequisite to the other levels. 
	\\nLocation: 650 S Orcas St\\\, Room 217\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98108 (In 
	Georgetown\\\, south of downtown\\\, with plenty of parking.) \\nMaximum S
	tudents: 16 \\nCost: Ticket price $295.00 \\nAge: 18 and above \\n**Cancel
	lation policy: If you must cancel before the first class\\\, we can only o
	ffer credit towards the same level class next quarter. We are unable to of
	fer refunds. If you cancel after the first class we cannot offer credit to
	wards a future class. Again\\\, we are unable to offer refunds.\n\nhttps:/
	/www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/improv-100-saturdays-intro-to-improv-
	say-yes-spring26/\n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/improv-100-saturdays-intro-
	to-improv-say-yes-spring26/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions Improv School ISSAQUAH/EASTSIDE\\\, 1315 NW
	 Mall Street\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA\\\, 98108\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fRc51F_0HgSrYTLNTULXe
SUMMARY:Improv Happy Hour
DTSTAMP:20260306T002950Z
DTSTART:20260321T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Our quick-thinking performers turn your suggestions into hilari
	ous scenes on the spot\\\, from movie mashups to literary spoofs and bold\
	\\, experimental comedy\\\, our quick-thinking performers turn. This famil
	y-friendly show at the iconic Gum Wall in Pike Place Market guarantees a n
	ight of laughter\\\, surprises\\\, and improv magic you won’t forget. Brin
	g your wildest ideas\\\, your loudest laughs\\\, and get ready for a one-o
	f-a-kind comedy experience—because at Improv Happy Hour\\\, anything can h
	appen (and usually does)!\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/i
	mprov-happy-hour-4-2-2/2026-03-21/\n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/improv-happy-hour-4-2-2/202
	6-03-21/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\\\, 1428 Post Alley at the Gum Wall in Pike
	 Place Market\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98101\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Dg942MVFYoOJY3d8Ef4kL
SUMMARY:Seattle Suites: An Improvised Neil Simon Comedy
DTSTAMP:20260306T002950Z
DTSTART:20260321T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Improvised comedy in the style of Neil Simon\\\, where one hote
	l suite becomes a comedic pressure cooker for 3 hilarious improvised tales
	\\n\\n\\n\\nOne hotel suite. Countless misunderstandings. Relentless laugh
	s. \\nSeattle Suite is a laugh-driven\\\, fully improvised play inspired b
	y the style of Plaza Suite and California Suite\\\, capturing the signatur
	e humor of Neil Simon that is fast\\\, verbal\\\, and rooted in beautifull
	y human flaws. Each night\\\, a single Seattle hotel room becomes the sett
	ing for interconnected scenes inspired by your suggestions\\\, friends ove
	rshare and spiral\\\, romantic gestures go wrong\\\, awkward silences stre
	tch\\\, and small problems become big ones. The comedy comes from characte
	r and relationship\\\, building through sharp dialogue\\\, escalating tens
	ion\\\, and recognizable\\\, lived-in situations. Perfect for fans of smar
	t comedy\\\, relationship humor\\\, and classic theatrical wit.\n\nhttps:/
	/www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/seattle-suites-an-improvised-neil-sim
	on-comedy/2026-03-21/\n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/seattle-suites-an-improvise
	d-neil-simon-comedy/2026-03-21/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\\\, 1428 Post Alley at the Gum Wall in Pike
	 Place Market\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98101\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:gPaOx1_xxSWHziwBt5CFg
SUMMARY:Ain't Misbehavin'
DTSTAMP:20260306T002950Z
DTSTART:20260321T210000Z
DESCRIPTION:The Fats Waller Music Show by Richard Maltby Jr.\n\nThe Fats Wa
	ller Musical Show The club is alive\, the band is swingin’\, and the music
	 of a jazz legend brings the house down. This immersive musical revue cele
	brates the life of Fats Waller on stage with joy\, rhythm\, and soul. Reme
	mbering his generation-defining songs and lasting impact on today’s music\
	, this exuberant Tony Award-winning tribute to Black artistry sings\, laug
	hs\, hopes\, and lives out loud.\n\nhttps://web.ovationtix.com/trs/pe.c/37
	019\n\nFrom Taproot Theatre
URL:https://web.ovationtix.com/trs/pe.c/37019
LOCATION:Taproot Theatre\, 204 N 85th St\, Seattle\, WA 98103
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:taproot
CATEGORIES:Taproot Theatre
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:4CGGH2Ttl_ilZddmhs-DP
SUMMARY:Seattle Theatresports 2026
DTSTAMP:20260306T002950Z
DTSTART:20260321T213000Z
DESCRIPTION:Seattle’s high-energy improv battle where your suggestions shap
	e every scene. Fast\\\, funny\\\, unpredictable comedy Fri. & Sat. 9:30\\n
	\\n\\n\\nWelcome to Seattle’s funnest improv comedy show\\\, a high-energy
	\\\, no-rules showdown where your ideas shape every scene. Seattle Theatre
	sports at Unexpected Productions’ Market Theater in Pike Place Market is p
	art comedy battle\\\, part game night\\\, and completely powered by the cr
	owd. Boo the judges. Cheer the Gum Wall race and laugh til it hurts! \\nEv
	ery show\\\, two teams of top Seattle improvisers go head to head\\\, perf
	orming games\\\, stories\\\, characters\\\, and scenes inspired entirely b
	y your suggestions. Judges score the rounds\\\, decide the winners\\\, and
	 shape the fun (as we boo them). No scripts. No safety nets. Just fast thi
	nking\\\, bold choices\\\, and pure creative mayhem. \\nThis isn’t your pa
	rents’ improv show\\\, unless your parents were super cool.\n\nhttps://www
	.unexpectedproductions.org/event/seattle-theatresports-2026-test/2026-03-2
	1/\n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/seattle-theatresports-2026-
	test/2026-03-21/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\\\, 1428 Post Alley at the Gum Wall in Pike
	 Place Market\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98101\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
